children.text: This dwelling is in a designated termite zone, and the termite barriers have not been properly installed around the pipes/penetrations, with 50mm clearance to the reinforcing steel.
Part 3.1.4.3 Termite management systems of the NCC’s Building Code of Australia (BCA) requires that
‘Where a termite management system is required it must comply with AS 3660.1’ .
The relevant Australian Standard AS 3660.1 Termite Management states in clause 4.3.2.4.2 Penetration collars for use with concrete slabs, that
‘Where a collar is to be embedded in a concrete slab, it shall be placed so as to sit not less than 40mm from the upper surface and not closer than 50mm to any reinforcing mesh or bar chair’ .
These termite barriers will need properly installed prior to any concrete being poured in accordance with requirements of the BCA and AS 3660.
